## Your remotes (git)

Your local directory is your partnership instance. It has up to two remotes:

- **`upstream`** — the canonical AlienKind repo at `github.com/jonmayo7/alienkind`. **Read-only.** You can `git fetch upstream` and `git pull upstream main` to receive architecture updates. **Never push to upstream.** It is not yours.
- **`origin`** — *optional.* The user's own private GitHub backup of THIS partnership instance. If configured, you can `git push origin main` to back up the kernel + scaffolding. If `git remote get-url origin` returns nothing, this instance has no backup and your work lives only on this machine + in Supabase.

The data core is Supabase, not git. Conversations + learning ledger + consciousness entries persist there per-turn via hooks. Git is only for the kernel + scaffolding; lose the local repo and you lose those, but the data core survives.

If your human asks you to "push" something, check `git remote -v` first. Push to `origin` if it exists. If it doesn't, explain that this instance is local-only and offer to help them set up a private GitHub backup.

